    "discriminators": [
     "A CLUSTER, not an event: many metallic onsets scattered irregularly over seconds (transient_count >= 3, typically 8-30; low onset_periodicity). METAL-IMPACT is one onset; that is the axis.",
     "Ring is metallic and long as in METAL-IMPACT, so timbre cannot separate them - only onset count, onset_rate_per_second and length can.",
     "Against METAL-BREAK: BREAK is a single failure event front-loaded on a fracture crack; CRASH & DEBRIS is a fall/collapse whose onsets are spread across the file with a decaying settle (higher envelope_temporal_centroid).",
     "Against CHAINS-MOVEMENT: chain jingle has far more, far smaller, far more evenly-dense onsets and almost no low_band_energy."
    ],
