    "discriminators": [
     "Sustained high-centroid contact - scrapes, creaks, squeaks, squeals, screeches. Defined by a HELD, restless spectrum: high spectral_centroid_hz with high spectral_centroid_deviation_hz (partials wander and jump as stick-slip re-locks).",
     "Not impulsive: low crest_factor and high sustain_ratio are the hard boundary against METAL-IMPACT and METAL-BREAK.",
     "Against METAL-TONAL: FRICTION is unstable and noisy (low harmonicity, wandering centroid); TONAL is a stable, high-harmonicity ring.",
     "Brighter and more partial-driven than ROCKS-FRICTION (a dull granular grind) and than DIRT & SAND scraping (near-flat broadband granular hiss)."
